Uttar Pradesh assembly elections 2017 Live updates: Fifth phase of voting begins Uttar Pradesh assembly elections 2017 Live updates: Fifth phase of voting begins Uttar Pradesh assembly elections 2017 Live updates: Fifth phase of voting begins By: Express Web Desk | New Delhi | Updated: February 27, 2017 7:10 am (Representational Image) 
The 51 Assembly constituencies spread across 11 districts of Uttar Pradesh go to polls on Monday. These constituencies include Amethi, Sultanpur, and Bahraich and Shravasti in Terai region. The voting for the state that began on February 11, with the first phase, will end on March 8 with the seventh phase. The counting of votes will take place on March 11. 
Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Akhilesh Yadav said Sunday that the SP-Congress alliance between two youth leaders would change the course of politics at the national and state levels. The SP chief’s remark at an election rally in Maharajganj came after BJP president Amit Shah had called the pre-poll alliance as one “between two corrupt families – one from Delhi and the other from Lucknow.”
